  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting Food Security through Agriculture-based Livelihood Activities in flood-affected areas of Swat</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Affected population(s), Women</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Base Line Study Formation of Village committes for Men and Women in each targeted village; Trainings of men and women on leadership and community management skills; Capacity building training of farmers on integrated crop management, horticulture, seeds preservation and poultry management; Trainings of women on Kitchen Gardenning; Training of farmers on orchard management; Distribution of fruit plants among the beneficiaries; Provision of agriculture inputs to the target farmers; Project End-Line Assessment &amp;amp; Audit</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Church World Service Pakistan/Afghanistan has designed this project to address the food security issues of 1900 women and men farmers&#x2019; families in Union Council Bashigram.  The project activities include vouchers to be used during market days for the purchase of seeds, fertilizers &amp;amp; agriculture tools generally to support main crops and 200 vouchers exclusively for female farmers to raise Kitchen gardens by procuring necessary vegetable seeds and some tools, distribution of fruit trees, capacity building of both male and female agriculture farmers on Integrated Crop Management and fruit tree management. Women farmers will be trained on livestock management.  Special trainings will be organized on the Disaster Risk Management for the community organizations members to enable them to cope any disaster in future.</narrative>
  </description>
